<item>
 <title>Git-Flow &amp; disposable testing sites</title>
 <link>https://dev-2014drupalcampcoloradoorg.pantheonsite.io/session/git-flow-disposable-testing-sites</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;This session will demonstrate how easily you can create Drupal 7 &amp;amp; 8 testing sites from any git-flow branch... even feature branches. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is particularly useful for testing where you need to create a site for each feature branch, see if your fixes are working, share/show the features working to your clients, and then merge your changes into Development branch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#039;ll also demonstrate how these sites can be automatically updated when particular git-flow branches are updated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This session will assume that you know git-flow and you&#039;re working with multiple developers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-experience-level field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;Experience level:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div &gt;Advanced&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-field-track field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-inline clearfix&quot;&gt;&lt;div &gt;Track:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div &gt;&lt;div &gt;DevOps&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
